<plot>Film Next Round is a negation to Akira Kurusowa's Rashomon. Eastern philosophy says, to negate the guru is to demonstrate his teachings. While Rashomon depicts that an incident if heard from different people will give rise to a totally different element, the film Next Round makes an attempt to show that an incident if thought together by various people can be still the same. This makes it important for an enlightened society that we live in.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?394727</url></doc>
